-- South Africa Cancels $160 Million of Debt Owed by Cuba to Bolster Trade
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-12-08T05:26:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-08/south-africa-cancels-160-million-of-debt-owed-by-cuba-to-bolster-trade.html
South Africa will cancel 1.1 billion
rand of debt owed by Cuba in an effort to boost trade between
the two countries, the African nation’s Trade and Industry
Minister Rob Davies said.  South Africa will also offer 70 million rand of extended
credit lines, 40 million rand of support to Cuba for seeds and
fertilizers and 100 million rand from its African Renaissance
Fund to fund purchases from Africa’s largest economy, he said in
a statement posted on the presidency’s website, dated yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  